<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers\Xenoraa;

use App\Http\Controllers\Controller;
use App\Models\User;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;

class XenoraaController extends Controller
{
    public function home()
    {
        $stats = [
            'total_users'    => User::count(),
            'showcase_users' => User::where('status', 'active')->whereNotNull('username')->take(6)->get(),
        ];
        return view('xenoraa.home', compact('stats'));
    }

    public function features()
    {
        return view('xenoraa.features');
    }

    public function pricing()
    {
        return view('xenoraa.pricing');
    }

    public function showcase()
    {
        $users = User::where('status', 'active')
            ->whereNotNull('username')
            ->withCount(['blogPosts'])
            ->latest()
            ->get();
        return view('xenoraa.showcase', compact('users'));
    }

    public function blog()
    {
        $posts = \App\Models\BlogPost::where('status', 'published')
            ->whereIn('slug', [
                'indian-businesses-unified-saas-platform',
                'xenoraa-vs-5-tools-cost-comparison',
                'freelance-consultant-digital-presence-xenoraa',
                'crm-guide-small-businesses-india-2026',
                'launch-online-store-no-code-xenoraa',
                'xenoraa-business-os-unified-dashboard',
                'outgrown-spreadsheets-switch-to-crm',
                'pos-ecommerce-unified-inventory',
                'build-professional-website-30-minutes-xenoraa',
                'disconnected-tools-data-silos-business-growth',
            ])
            ->orderBy('published_at', 'desc')
            ->get();
        $featured = $posts->first();
        $gridPosts = $posts->skip(1)->values();
        return view('xenoraa.blog', compact('posts', 'featured', 'gridPosts'));
    }

    public function blogShow($slug)
    {
        $post = \App\Models\BlogPost::where('slug', $slug)
            ->where('status', 'published')
            ->firstOrFail();
        $related = \App\Models\BlogPost::where('status', 'published')
            ->where('id', '!=', $post->id)
            ->whereIn('slug', [
                'indian-businesses-unified-saas-platform',
                'xenoraa-vs-5-tools-cost-comparison',
                'freelance-consultant-digital-presence-xenoraa',
                'crm-guide-small-businesses-india-2026',
                'launch-online-store-no-code-xenoraa',
                'xenoraa-business-os-unified-dashboard',
                'outgrown-spreadsheets-switch-to-crm',
                'pos-ecommerce-unified-inventory',
                'build-professional-website-30-minutes-xenoraa',
                'disconnected-tools-data-silos-business-growth',
            ])
            ->orderBy('published_at', 'desc')
            ->limit(3)
            ->get();
        return view('xenoraa.blog-show', compact('post', 'related'));
    }

    public function getStarted()
    {
        return view('xenoraa.get-started');
    }

    public function about()
    {
        return view('xenoraa.about');
    }

    public function careers()
    {
        return view('xenoraa.careers');
    }


    // ── Documentation Hub ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    private function docsData(): array
    {
        return [
        [
            'section_id' => 'getting_started',
            'slug'       => 'getting-started',
            'title'      => 'Getting Started with Xenoraa',
            'subtitle'   => 'Your first steps to setting up and launching your Xenoraa platform.',
            'icon'       => 'fa-rocket',
            'content'    => '
# Getting Started with Xenoraa

Welcome to Xenoraa, your comprehensive platform for managing your business operations. This guide will walk you through the essential steps to set up your account, configure your domain, and understand your tenant dashboard, ensuring a smooth and successful launch.

## 1. Account Setup and Onboarding

Your journey with Xenoraa begins with a straightforward account setup process, followed by an intuitive onboarding experience designed to get you acquainted with the platform\'s core functionalities.

### 1.1 Creating Your Account

To begin, navigate to the Xenoraa website and click on the \'Sign Up\' or \'Get Started\' button. Follow the prompts to enter your details, including your email address and a secure password. Once registered, you will receive a verification email. Please click the link in this email to activate your account.

### 1.2 Initial Onboarding

Upon your first login, Xenoraa provides a guided onboarding experience. This tour highlights key areas of your dashboard and introduces you to the various modules available. We recommend completing this tour to familiarize yourself with the platform\'s layout and capabilities.

## 2. Domain Mapping and DNS Setup

Connecting your custom domain to Xenoraa is crucial for establishing your brand identity and ensuring a professional online presence. This section details how to map your domain and configure your DNS settings.

### 2.1 Understanding Domain Mapping

Domain mapping allows you to use your existing domain name (e.g., `yourbusiness.com`) with your Xenoraa-powered website or services instead of a default Xenoraa subdomain. This enhances brand recognition and user trust.

### 2.2 Step-by-Step Domain Mapping

1.  **Access Domain Settings**: From your Xenoraa tenant dashboard, navigate to `Settings` > `Domain Management`.
2.  **Add Custom Domain**: Enter your desired custom domain name (e.g., `www.yourbusiness.com` or `shop.yourbusiness.com`) into the provided field and click `Add Domain`.
3.  **Retrieve DNS Records**: Xenoraa will generate specific DNS records (typically A records and CNAME records) that you need to add to your domain registrar.

### 2.3 Configuring DNS Records

To complete domain mapping, you must update your domain\'s DNS settings with your domain registrar (e.g., GoDaddy, Namecheap, Cloudflare). The exact steps may vary slightly depending on your registrar, but the general process is as follows:

1.  **Log in to your Domain Registrar**: Access your domain registrar\'s control panel.
2.  **Navigate to DNS Management**: Look for sections like `DNS Management`, `Advanced DNS`, or `Zone Editor`.
3.  **Add/Modify Records**: Create or modify the following records as provided by Xenoraa:
    *   **A Record**: Point your root domain (e.g., `@` or `yourbusiness.com`) to Xenoraa\'s IP address.
    *   **CNAME Record**: Point your subdomain (e.g., `www`) to the Xenoraa-provided hostname.

    *Example DNS Configuration Table:*

    | Type  | Host/Name | Value/Points To | TTL   |
    | :---- | :-------- | :-------------- | :---- |
    | A     | @         | [Xenoraa IP Address] | Auto  |
    | CNAME | www       | [Xenoraa Hostname] | Auto  |

4.  **Save Changes**: Save your DNS settings. DNS changes can take up to 24-48 hours to propagate globally.

## 3. SSL Activation

Secure Sockets Layer (SSL) is vital for encrypting data between your users and your Xenoraa platform, ensuring data privacy and building trust. Xenoraa simplifies this process with automatic SSL activation.

### 3.1 Importance of SSL

An active SSL certificate displays a padlock icon in the browser\'s address bar and changes your website\'s URL from `http://` to `https://`. This indicates a secure connection, which is essential for e-commerce, customer data protection, and SEO.

### 3.2 Automatic SSL Activation

Once your domain\'s DNS records have successfully propagated and point to Xenoraa, our system will automatically detect the changes and provision an SSL certificate for your custom domain. This process typically completes within a few hours after DNS propagation. You do not need to take any manual steps for SSL activation.

### 3.3 Troubleshooting SSL Issues

If your SSL certificate does not activate within 24 hours after DNS propagation, consider the following:

*   **DNS Propagation**: Double-check that your DNS records are correctly configured and have fully propagated. You can use online DNS lookup tools to verify.
*   **Domain Mapping**: Ensure your domain is correctly mapped within your Xenoraa dashboard.
*   **Contact Support**: If issues persist, please contact Xenoraa support with your domain name and a description of the problem.

## 4. Tenant Dashboard Overview

The Xenoraa tenant dashboard is your central hub for managing all aspects of your business. It provides a comprehensive overview of your operations, analytics, and access to all integrated modules.

### 4.1 Key Sections of the Dashboard

*   **Dashboard Home**: Provides a quick summary of key metrics, recent activities, and important notifications.
*   **Modules**: Access all your activated Xenoraa modules (e.g., Website Builder, E-commerce Store, CRM Sales).
*   **Analytics**: Detailed reports and insights into your website traffic, sales performance, and customer behavior.
*   **Settings**: Configure general platform settings, user management, integrations, and billing information.
*   **Notifications**: View system alerts, updates, and messages.

### 4.2 Navigating Your Dashboard

The dashboard is designed for intuitive navigation. Use the sidebar menu to switch between different modules and settings. The search bar at the top allows you to quickly find specific features or data. Regularly review your dashboard home for critical updates and performance insights.

## Conclusion

By following these steps, you will have successfully set up your Xenoraa account, mapped your custom domain, secured it with SSL, and gained familiarity with your tenant dashboard. You are now ready to explore Xenoraa\'s powerful modules and grow your business.',
