## Manage Your Xenoraa Subscriptions, Apps, and Invoices

Welcome to the Xenoraa Billing & Subscriptions module! This guide will walk you through understanding your subscription options, managing your applications, reviewing your invoice history, and handling your account settings. Xenoraa is designed to provide flexible and scalable solutions for your business needs.

---

### Understanding Xenoraa Subscription Tiers

Xenoraa offers three distinct subscription tiers tailored to different business sizes and requirements. Each tier provides a unique set of features and access to various modules. Understanding these tiers will help you choose the best fit for your operations.

#### Solo Tier

The **Solo** tier is ideal for individual entrepreneurs, freelancers, or small businesses just starting out. It provides essential tools to manage core business functions efficiently.

*   **Key Features:** Basic access to core modules, limited user accounts.
*   **Best For:** Single-user operations, testing the waters, minimal operational needs.

#### Duo Tier

The **Duo** tier is designed for growing businesses and small teams that require more collaborative features and expanded module access. It builds upon the Solo tier by offering enhanced capabilities.

*   **Key Features:** Expanded module access, multiple user accounts, advanced features for collaboration.
*   **Best For:** Small teams, businesses with moderate operational complexity, those needing more robust tools.

#### All-Access Tier

The **All-Access** tier is the most comprehensive offering, perfect for established businesses and larger teams that need full access to all Xenoraa modules and advanced functionalities. This tier ensures you have every tool necessary to scale and optimize your business.

*   **Key Features:** Full access to all Xenoraa modules, unlimited user accounts, priority support, advanced analytics, and custom integrations.
*   **Best For:** Large businesses, enterprises, operations requiring extensive features and maximum scalability.

#### Tier Comparison

To help you decide, here\'s a quick comparison of the key aspects of each tier:

| Feature/Tier        | Solo                               | Duo                                      | All-Access                                   |
| :------------------ | :--------------------------------- | :--------------------------------------- | :------------------------------------------- |
| **Target Audience** | Individuals, Small Businesses      | Growing Businesses, Small Teams          | Established Businesses, Large Teams          |
| **User Accounts**   | Limited                            | Multiple                                 | Unlimited                                    |
| **Module Access**   | Core Modules                       | Expanded Modules                         | All Modules                                  |
| **Support**         | Standard                           | Enhanced                                 | Priority                                     |
| **Advanced Features** | Basic                              | Moderate                                 | Comprehensive                                |

---

### Choosing and Switching Apps

Xenoraa allows you to customize your experience by choosing and switching between available applications (modules) based on your subscription tier. This flexibility ensures you only pay for what you need.

#### How to Browse Available Apps

1.  **Navigate to the \'Apps\' Section:** From your Xenoraa dashboard, locate and click on the "Apps" or "Modules" section in the sidebar menu.
2.  **Explore Categories:** Browse through different categories or use the search bar to find specific applications.
3.  **View Details:** Click on any app to see its description, features, and compatibility with your current subscription tier.

#### How to Add/Remove Apps

1.  **Select an App:** In the "Apps" section, choose the application you wish to add or remove.
2.  **Action Button:** Click the "Add to Subscription" or "Remove from Subscription" button. Note that some core apps might not be removable.
3.  **Confirm Changes:** Review the summary of changes to your subscription and confirm. Any changes to your billing will be clearly displayed.

#### Impact of Switching Apps/Tiers

*   **Upgrading:** If you upgrade your tier or add more apps, the changes will take effect immediately, and your billing will be prorated.
*   **Downgrading/Removing Apps:** If you downgrade your tier or remove apps, the changes will typically take effect at the start of your next billing cycle. You will retain access to the removed apps until the end of the current cycle.

---

### Invoice History

Keep track of all your payments and billing details through the Invoice History section. This allows for easy reconciliation and record-keeping.

#### How to View Past Invoices

1.  **Access Billing:** Go to the "Billing & Subscriptions" section from your dashboard.
2.  **Invoice History Tab:** Click on the "Invoice History" or "Payments" tab.
3.  **Browse Invoices:** A list of all your past invoices will be displayed, sorted by date.

#### How to Download Invoices

1.  **Select Invoice:** From the Invoice History list, click on the specific invoice you wish to download.
2.  **Download Option:** Look for a "Download PDF" or "Print" button and click it to save a copy of your invoice.

#### Understanding Invoice Details

Each invoice provides a detailed breakdown of your charges, including:

*   **Invoice Number:** Unique identifier for the transaction.
*   **Billing Period:** The dates covered by the invoice.
*   **Items:** A list of subscribed apps/services and their respective costs.
*   **Discounts/Credits:** Any applied discounts or credits.
*   **Total Amount Due:** The final amount charged.
*   **Payment Status:** Indicates if the invoice has been paid or is pending.

---

### Account Management

Managing your billing account ensures uninterrupted service and allows you to update your payment information as needed.

#### Updating Payment Methods

1.  **Go to Account Settings:** In the "Billing & Subscriptions" section, find "Payment Methods" or "Account Settings."
2.  **Add/Edit Card:** You can add a new credit/debit card or edit existing payment details.
3.  **Set as Default:** Choose a default payment method for automatic renewals.

#### Changing Billing Cycles

Depending on your subscription, you might have the option to switch between monthly or annual billing cycles. Annual billing often comes with a discount.

1.  **Billing Cycle Options:** Look for "Billing Cycle" in your account settings.
2.  **Select Cycle:** Choose your preferred cycle (e.g., Monthly, Annually).
3.  **Confirm:** Confirm the change; prorated charges or credits may apply.

#### Cancelling Subscriptions

We understand that business needs change. If you need to cancel your subscription:

1.  **Cancellation Option:** In "Account Settings" or "Billing & Subscriptions," find the "Cancel Subscription" option.
2.  **Follow Prompts:** You may be asked for feedback or confirmation. Your subscription will typically remain active until the end of your current billing period.

#### Contacting Support for Billing Issues

If you encounter any issues or have questions not covered in this guide, our support team is ready to assist.

1.  **Access Support:** Navigate to the "Help" or "Support" section of your Xenoraa dashboard.
2.  **Submit a Ticket:** Choose the option to submit a support ticket, detailing your billing query.
3.  **Live Chat/Phone:** For urgent matters, check if live chat or phone support is available for your tier.

---

### Troubleshooting & FAQs

Here are answers to some common questions regarding billing and subscriptions.

**Q: What happens if my payment fails?**

A: If a payment fails, you will be notified via email. We will attempt to re-process the payment after a few days. Please ensure your payment method is up-to-date to avoid service interruption.

**Q: Can I upgrade or downgrade my subscription at any time?**

A: Yes, you can upgrade or downgrade your subscription at any time. Upgrades are usually effective immediately, with prorated billing. Downgrades typically take effect at the start of your next billing cycle.

**Q: Where can I find my next billing date?**

A: Your next billing date is usually displayed in the "Billing & Subscriptions" section of your account dashboard, often under "Subscription Details" or "Next Payment Due."

**Q: Is my billing information secure?**

A: Yes, Xenoraa uses industry-standard encryption and security protocols to protect your billing information. Your payment details are handled by secure payment gateways.',
